  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To his Friend.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>OF <hi>Vice,</hi> whose <hi>Counter-mine</hi> a state confounds,</l>
      <l>Worse then <hi>Sedition:</hi> of those Mortall <hi>Woundes</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Which (throughly search'd) doe <hi>Kingdomes</hi> hearts endanger:</l>
      <l>Of <hi>Plagues</hi> that o're run Citties: of those stranger</l>
      <l>
         <hi>Big-swolne Impostumes,</hi> poisning the strong health</l>
      <l>Of the most <hi>Sound,</hi> best <hi>Dieted Common-wealth,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Thou tell'st the <hi>Causes,</hi> and doest teach the <hi>Cure,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>By <hi>Mea'cine</hi> well-compounded, cheape, and sure:</l>
      <l>And (as <hi>One</hi> read in deepe <hi>Chirurgery,)</hi>
      </l>
      <l>Draw'st of these <hi>Eu'lls,</hi> the true Anatomy.</l>
      <l>Then, on thy <hi>Plainnesse</hi> let none lay reproofe,</l>
      <l>Thou tak'st <hi>Sinne's</hi> heigth (as men doe starres) aloofe.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>M: R:</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
